JOHANNESBURG - Furniture retailer Lewis is warning shareholders that its earnings will decline by 18 percent. The company will release financial results next month. Lewis on Friday blamed the drop in hire-purchase sales as the reason for declining earnings. This followed the National Credit Regulator's enforcement of credit-affordability assessments. READ:Â Lewis Stores wins battle against club fee charges Lewis recently acquired United Furniture Outlets for R320-million, saying it intended to target upper-income customers. The furniture retailer said this would help the group sell more furniture for cash rather than credit. eNCA